
Statement:-
===========

# It is used when required a single time use of sql statement.

# It is faster as compare to Prepared Statement.

# It is difficult when use values in concatenation form.

# It does not support placeholder inputs.

# If there is multiple data retrival command then it will take time
  as compare to Prepared Statement. 
  
  
  
Prepared Statement :-
=====================

# It is best to use when multiple times need to use same sql statement.
(like = select * from emp)

# It is compatible with placeholder values so that we can write sql
statement without concatenation.

# It implements Statement Interface so it has accessibility of all the
Statement methods along with it's specific methods.








